  "prompt": "How do I embed a Prezi into an HTML email?",
  "response": "To embed a Prezi in an HTML email, follow these steps:\n\n1. Get the Prezi Share Link:\n- Open your Prezi\n- Click \"Share\" \n- Select \"Get embed code\"\n- Copy the provided iframe embed code\n\n2. Insert the iframe in your HTML email:\n```html\n<iframe \n  src=\"YOUR_PREZI_EMBED_URL\" \n  width=\"550\" \n  height=\"400\" \n  frameborder=\"0\" \n  allowfullscreen>\n</iframe>\n```\n\nImportant Considerations:\n- Not all email clients support iframes\n- Gmail and Outlook may block or disable embedded content\n- Consider alternative approaches:\n  - Include a clickable screenshot/thumbnail linking to Prezi\n  - Use a \"View Presentation\" text/button link\n  - Provide a direct URL to the Prezi\n\nRecommended Fallback Strategy:\n```html\n<a href=\"DIRECT_PREZI_URL\">\n  <img src=\"PREZI_THUMBNAIL_IMAGE\" alt=\"Click to view Prezi\">\n</a>\n```\n\nTest your email in multiple email clients to ensure compatibility.",
